programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Monuments & Landmarks
programme.desc: Many of the world’s most significant manmade wonders serve not as dwellings, but as powerful signposts. But more than giving us direction, they tell us a story - they characterize powerful forces, or commemorate power lost.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Arks
programme.desc: Cut off from continents, remote islands have become floating arks, attracting migrating species and forging new ones. Take a privileged glimpse into the secret lives of the rare and exotic species that inhabit these lost worlds.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Water Adventures
programme.desc: We are captivated by oceans, rivers, and lakes - the power, the flow, the reflective stillness. And as we seek to get closer, we immerse ourselves in an expanding range of aquatic experiences.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Nearshore Islands
programme.desc: Some of the world’s greatest islands are so close that they blend in with the mainland. But regardless of their size and origins, they are often the islands we are drawn to the most, each forging their own unique identity.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Remote Cities
programme.desc: Brave the frontiers of the world’s most remote cities. More than distant trading posts and isolated regional hubs, cities like Alice Springs, Jaipur and even Las Vegas serve as gateways to the wild places of the Earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coasts
programme.desc: Along coasts, one element ends and another begins. No two days are ever the same on a coastline: the only thing that remains a constant is the timeless power of the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Grassland Animals
programme.desc: Grasslands are the great stages of the natural world where large animals play out spectacular lives in clear view of people, including lions, leopards, elephants, rhinoceros, cheetahs, impalas, kangaroos, wallaby, potoroo, bison, and wolves.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The 1920s and 30s were uncertain times for the RAF as well as all other armed services. With peace came cuts in spending on new aircraft development.

programme.title: RAF: The Royal Air Force: Battle for the Skies
programme.desc: The series begins before WWI when military commanders struggled to understand what uses aviation might have. The Wright Brothers had been the first to fly a powered aircraft in controlled flight in 1903, but even by 1914 aircraft were still underpowered.
programme.sub-title: Useless for the Purposes of War

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Franz Stangl & Gustav Wagner
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Nazi hunter Simon Wiesenthal tracked down fugitive war criminal Franz Stangl in Brazil. Stangl was responsible for the murder of over 800,000 people.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Paul Touvier
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how French investigators hunted down Paul Touvier a pro-Nazi sympathizer who was responsible for murdering both Jews and resistance fighters.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Kurt Lischka
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters looks at how German housewife Beate Klarsfeld and her husband Serge helped track down former Paris Gestapo chief Kurt Lishka. Lishka ordered the arrest and murder of over 33,000 Jews.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Joseph Mengele
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Mossad agents from Israel spent nearly thirty years tracking the notorious Nazi physician Josef Mengele. After the war, Mengele flees to Argentina where he lives a relatively nondescript life.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Erich Priebke
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how, a half-century after the war, American journalists track down former Gestapo officer Erich Priebke. Priebke who was responsible for some of Italy's worst atrocities fled to Argentina after the war.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Klaus Barbie
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters looks at how the husband and wife team of Serge and Beate Klarsfeld worked tirelessly to have Nazi war criminal Klaus Barbie extradited from Bolvia to stand trail in France.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Adolf Eichmann
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines the capture of Adolf Eichmann considered by many to be one of the main architects of the Holocaust. Eichmann was captured outside of his home near Buenos Aires in Argentina by Mossad agents.

programme.title: Nazi Hunters: Herbert Cukurs
programme.desc: Nazi Hunters examines how Israeli secret service agents traveled to South America to assassinate Nazi war criminal Herbert Cukurs. Known as the Hangman of Riga, Cukurs was responsible for the deaths of over 30,000 Latvian Jews.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Hitler's Killer Police
programme.desc: In Ukraine and Lithuania, Nazi invaders were welcomed as liberators. In Lithuania, Antanas Gecas led a militia that executed hundreds of Jews. Ukrainian nationalists participated in pogroms slaughtering 34,000 Jews in two days.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Good Collaborators?
programme.desc: Finland defended itself in the Winter War under Marshal Mannerheim. Finland allied with Nazi Germany against the Soviet Union in 1941. Finland later negotiated peace with the Allies and switched sides as Nazi defeat became apparent.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Dutch Collaborator
programme.desc: Anton Adriaan Mussert, initially resisted Hitler’s anti-Semitism despite modeling his NSB party, even welcoming Jewish members. His failed attempt to kidnap Queen Wilhelmina led him into hiding, after which he collaborated in hopes of gaining power.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler
programme.desc: In Hitler’s Germany, those with Jewish ancestry faced harsh Nuremberg Laws. Full Jews faced death; Mischlinge endured discrimination, job bans. Some, like Helmut Schmidt, unaware of heritage, found protectors like Milch in high places.
programme.sub-title: The Jews Who Fought for Hitler

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Grand Mufti
programme.desc: The controversy surrounding Mohammad Amin al-Husayni, stems from his Nazi collaboration. He recruited Bosnian Muslims and advocated for a Palestinian homeland with Nazi help. His diaries reveal awareness of the Holocaust and anti-Semitic sentiments.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The IRA Conspiracy
programme.desc: During WWII, the IRA's "S Plan" aimed to bomb Britain, drawing German support to weaken the British. "Operation Green" and "Plan Kathleen" envisioned IRA aiding a German invasion of Northern Ireland, but both failed due to bungling and infighting.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: The Arajs Kommando
programme.desc: Viktor Arajs, a Latvian, played a significant role in the Holocaust, collaborating with the Nazis to eliminate Jews. Leading the Arajs Kommando, he orchestrated the killings of around 30,000 Jews. Arajs justified his actions as patriotic defense.

programme.title: NEW: Nazi Collaborators: Vidkun Quisling
programme.desc: Vidkun Quisling, once honored for diplomacy, turned traitor by collaborating with Nazis. His bid for power in Norway failed, relegated by Germans. Despite being named "fuehrer," his reign led to repression until his hanging post-Nazi defeat.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler: The film explores the roots of Adolf Hitler and traces the story of his life from the town of his birth to his final days.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: Largely due to the SS which he led, Himmler, the unsuspecting killer, was the most powerful of all of Hitler's men.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Josef Goebbels
programme.desc: Josef Goebbels: A unique documentary looking at the role of Goebbels, a man from Hitler's inner circle.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Julius Streicher
programme.desc: Julius Streicher: A look at the role of Julius Streicher in the Nazi regime. Streicher was responsible for much anti-Semitic propaganda

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Hermann Goering
programme.desc: Hermann Goering: Hermann Goering was the commander-in-chief of the Luftwaffe and Hitler's designated successor. This is his dark story.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Albert Speer
programme.desc: Albert Speer: The career of Albert Speer, Hitler's architect, is explored in this documentary of dark figures.

programme.title: A Glenbrooke Christmas
programme.desc: Longing to be accepted for herself and not just her wealth, an heiress heads to the small town of Glenbrooke, where she discovers the joys of a simple Christmas, community, and maybe even love.

programme.title: With Love, Christmas
programme.desc: Melanie Welch is a hard-working ad executive who finds herself teamed up with uptight coworker Donovan Goodwin to come up with the ultimate Christmas commercial for a new cell phone.

programme.title: A Christmas Treasure
programme.desc: After opening a 100-year-old time capsule and meeting a charming chef, Lou questions whether or not she should move to New York after Christmas and further her writing career.

programme.title: Nantucket Noel
programme.desc: During the Seaside Noel celebrations Christina learns of a developer who is planning to tear down the wharf that is home to her toy store. Tensions rise as she falls for the developer's son, Andy.

programme.title: A Gift Wrapped Christmas
programme.desc: A personal shopper Gwen's newest client, Charlie, is a high-rolling, workaholic, single father.

programme.title: Gingerbread Miracle
programme.desc: Two old friends from high school work together over Christmas to sell his uncle’s Mexican bakery, famous for its magical gingerbread cookies that grant wishes.

programme.title: Christmas Comes Twice
programme.desc: Cheryl is the top newscaster who has achieved her dreams but has regrets about the guy who got away five years earlier. When the Christmas carnival comes to town, a ride around the carousel takes her back in time...

programme.title: Christmas Festival of Ice
programme.desc: When Emma finds out that her beloved ice-sculpting contest, part of her hometown's Christmas festival, has been canceled, she springs into action.

programme.title: Christmas She Wrote
programme.desc: When Kayleigh, a romance writer, has her column cancelled right before Christmas, she heads home to reconnect with her family. Kayleigh gets an unexpected visit from the man who cancelled her column.

programme.title: A Godwink Christmas: Miracle of Love
programme.desc: Brought together by community service, Eric and Joy find new purpose at Christmas. As they help a family rebuild their home, coincidences and a medical miracle lead them to believe in destiny.

programme.title: A Godwink Christmas: Second Chance, First Love
programme.desc: After 15 years, Pat moves home from Hawaii with his two sons and through a series of coincidences, or Godwinks, ends up stuck in traffic next to his high school sweetheart, Margie at Christmas.

programme.title: Unarchived
programme.desc: In community archives across British Columbia, local knowledge keepers are fighting for a more inclusive history through family photos, newspaper articles and deeply rooted memories.

programme.title: Doctor Lawyer Indian Chief
programme.desc: A tribute to Indigenous women everywhere, this short documentary focuses on 5 women from across Canada. They talk about the importance of Indigenous culture in helping them to develop a sense of self and seeing through rough times.

programme.title: Kanehsatake 270 Years Of Resistance
programme.desc: In July 1990, a dispute over a proposed golf course to be built on Kanien'kéhaka (Mohawk) lands in Oka, Quebec, set the stage for an historic confrontation that would grab international headlines and sear itself into the Canadian consciousness.

programme.title: Lipsett Diaries
programme.desc: Lipsett Diaries is a descent into the maelstrom of anguish that tormented famed Canadian experimental filmmaker Arthur Lipsett, who died prematurely at age 49.

programme.title: Firewords Louky Bersianik Jovette Marchessault Nicole Brossa
programme.desc: Firewords offers an intimate glimpse of three respected, controversial Québec writers.Louky Bersianik, Jovette Marchessault and Nicole Brossard have contributed greatly to the creation of a distinctive women's literature.

programme.title: Vendetta Song
programme.desc: Filmmaker Eylem Kaftan unravels her aunt's 30-year-old murder mystery in Kurdish Turkey. "Vendetta Song" explores customs and Eylem's quest for closure amid political instability and potential retribution.

programme.title: Canada Vignettes June In Povungnituk - Quebec Arctic
programme.desc: On a beautiful summer’s day in Nunavik, a family enjoys the pleasures of berry picking and fishing as the sound of two Elders throat-singing fills the environment. Directed by Alanis Obomsawin as part of the Canada Vignettes series.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Women At War
programme.desc: This 1942 British film, Women at War, contrasts sharply with similar Canadian productions. It accepts women's direct participation in the war effort as a natural outgrowth of their peacetime occupations.

programme.title: Turnaround A Story Of Recovery
programme.desc: Turnaround: A Story of Recovery" follows five women battling addiction at Aurora House. This documentary offers insight for families, friends, and professionals interested in alternative treatment methods.

programme.title: Unwanted Soldiers
programme.desc: Filmmaker Jari Osborne discovers her father's WWII involvement, revealing discrimination against Chinese-Canadians. His secret missions in Southeast Asia shed light on their quiet heroism, paying moving tribute in this multi-layered documentary.

programme.title: Canada Vignettes Log Drivers Waltz
programme.desc: A young girl who loves to dance and is ready to marry chooses a log driver over his more well-to-do, land-loving competition. Driving logs down the river has made him the best dancing partner to be found.

programme.title: The Children Of Refus Global
programme.desc: In 1948, Borduas' manifesto marked Quebec's modernization. Filmmaker Manon Barbeau revisits, exploring its impact on descendants. Their childhoods, marked by abandonment, reveal art's transformative power in emotional reflection.

programme.title: Burning Times, The
programme.desc: This film is an in-depth look at the witch-hunts that swept through Europe just a few hundred years ago. False accusations and trials led to massive torture and burnings at the stake, and ultimately to the destruction of an organic way of life.

programme.title: Best Time Of My Life Portraits Of Women In Mid-Life, The
programme.desc: An upbeat, positive film about a group of women dealing with mid-life and menopause. The women come from a wide range of backgrounds, careers and lifestyles, it effectively dispels popular myths and fears about life during and after menopause.

programme.title: Totem Talk
programme.desc: Urban Indigenous teens embark on a surreal journey guided by a magical raven, encountering animated totem pole characters and exploring Northwest First Nation culture's significance. Featuring insights from artist J. Bradley Hunt.

programme.title: Cry Of The Wild
programme.desc: To hear Bill Mason tell about the making of this feature film (he is also the narrator) is to share with him his affection for his camera-quarry: the big northern timber wolves and pure-white Arctic wolves.

programme.title: Unspoken Tears Trauma Through Words
programme.desc: This powerful documentary explores the psychological scars of war and highlights the importance of understanding in successfully integrating refugee children into Quebec’s schools.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: My Christmas Love
programme.desc: Celeste ist Event-Managerin, der Advent ihre Hoch-Saison. Gleichzeitig muss sie sich um ihre Nichte Finley kümmern, die bei ihr lebt. Einzige Lösung: sie engagiert Kindermädchen Taylor. Doch die entpuppt sich als Mann...

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Die 12 Weihnachtsgeschenke
programme.desc: Als Anna, eine arbeitslose Malerin, nicht mehr über die Runden kommt, wird sie als persönliche Weihnachtseinkäuferin für Marc, einen verklemmten Firmenchef, eingestellt.

programme.title: Return To Christmas Creek
programme.desc: Eine junge Chefin kehrt in ihre Heimatstadt zurück, um die Bedeutung von Weihnachten wiederzuentdecken.

programme.title: Ich bin nicht bereit für Weihnachten
programme.desc: Hollys energiegeladenes, karriereorientiertes Leben gerat vollig aus den Fugem, als sie feststellt, dass sie nicht mehr lugen kann, weil der Weihnachtsmann ihrer Nichte Anna einen besonderen Wunsch erfullt hat.

programme.title: Weihnachten auf königliche Art
programme.desc: Kristin Cooper, die hübsche und talentierte Assistentin einer globalen PR-Firma, wird mit der Leitung der jährlichen Weihnachtsmodenschau und -auktion für den Bekleidungsunternehmer Mr. Carson beauftragt.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Weihnachtsmann aus Leidenschaft
programme.desc: Was wäre wohl, wenn der Weihnachtsmann in der Nachbarschaft leben würde? Es wäre ein Paradies für Kinder, nicht jedoch für eine junge Frau, die als Staatsanwältin tätig ist und sich für ihren Vater schämt.

programme.title: Simsalabim Sabrina: Weihnachtsstimmung
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten und Gems Selbstgefälligkeit macht alle verrückt. Sabrina will ihr die Augen öffnen. Sie inszeniert mit ihrer Familie eine Gespenster-Erscheinung wie in Charles Dickens' Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: Anthony Bourdain – Eine Frage des Geschmacks: Holiday Special
programme.desc: Eine Frage des Geschmacks setzt eine beliebte Festtagstradition fort – Tony erlebt ein ungewöhnliches und merkwürdiges Weihnachtsfest.

programme.title: Beverly Hills 90210: Ready Or Not
programme.desc: Dr. Monahan wirft Kelly aus der Klinik. Brandon und Steve stellen eine neue Assistentin namens Janet Sosna ein und holen David als Musikkritiker an Bord. Valerie macht einen Deal mit einem Buchmacher, der seine Geschäfte im „After Dark“ abwickelt.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Alone for Christmas
programme.desc: Wenn eine Familie an Heiligabend das Haus von Oma besucht, lässt sie ihren Hund allein zu Hause. Und wenn Einbrecher versuchen, die Geschenke unter dem Baum hervorzuholen, um sie zu stoppen.

programme.title: Weihnachten mit Hindernissen
programme.desc: Vicky und Jason haben sich schon längst getrennt. Aber ihre beiden Kinder bringen sie dazu, die Weihnachtsferien gemeinsam zu verbringen. Als dann auch noch Vickys Boss und Jasons Assistentin auftauchen, wird es immer turbulenter...

programme.title: Simsalabim Sabrina: Weihnachtsstimmung
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten und Gems Selbstgefälligkeit macht alle verrückt. Sabrina will ihr die Augen öffnen. Sie inszeniert mit ihrer Familie eine Gespenster-Erscheinung wie in Charles Dickens' Weihnachtsgeschichte.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Stille Nacht, heilige Nacht
programme.desc: Kurz vor Weihnachten willigt Buffalo Airways ein, die kanadische Polizei dabei zu unterstützen, Spielzeug und andere Geschenke in die entlegensten Regionen des Landes zu transportieren.

programme.title: Weihnachten In Rom
programme.desc: Lacey Chabert spielt die unabhängig denkende, amerikanische Stadtführerin Angela, die kurz vor Weihnachten ihren Job in Rom verliert. Als sie auf den New Yorker Top-Manager Oliver trifft, heuert er sie als seine Stadtführerin für die Ewige Stadt an.

programme.title: Wer an Wunder glaubt
programme.desc: Als junges Mädchen war Suzie (Hayden Panettiere, „Nashville\\") offenherzig, optimistisch und spielte auch gerne mal den ein oder anderen Streich. Aber als aus Suzie Susan wurde, verschwand ihre spielerische und einnehmende Persönlichkeit über die Jahre.

programme.title: Mein Weihnachtstraum
programme.desc: Um sich vor der gefürchteten Besitzerin eines Kaufhauses in Paris zu beweisen, bittet Managerin Christina den kürzlich gefeuerten Kurt um Hilfe in der Weihnachtszeit. Als die beiden sich näher kommen, muss Christina eine schwere Wahl treffen...

programme.title: Die Geschichte vom Weihnachtsengel
programme.desc: Eddie und sein Bruder möchten Weihnachten mit ihrer Mutter verbringen, die aber seit einem Autounfall schwer verletzt im Krankenhaus liegt. Eines Nachts träumt Eddie von seiner Mutter, die ihn darum bittet, einen Engel zu finden, damit sie...

programme.title: How To Rock: Wie man Weihnachten rockt
programme.desc: Kacey und ihre Freunde machen in der Mall Weihnachtseinkäufe. Sie vergessen die Zeit und merken nicht, dass sie eingeschlossen werden. Zu allem Unglück treffen sie auch auf Molly und Grace.

programme.title: Sissi: Die Nacht vor Weihnachten
programme.desc: Weihnachten in Wien ist nicht mehr so schön, wie es einmal war, seit Santa Claus eines seiner Renntiere abhanden gekommen ist. Nach einer Verletzungspause ist es nicht mehr heimgekehrt.

programme.title: All Grown Up: Der gestohlene Weihnachtsbaum
programme.desc: Chuckie grault es vor noch einem tristen Weihnachtsfest. Versehentlich stiehlt er den Weihnachtsbaum der Nachbarn...

programme.title: Regal Academy: Die Schneekönigin
programme.desc: Um sich an den sechs großen Märchenfamilien zu rächen, macht sich die Schneekönigin an die kleinen Kürbis Pompoms, die Roses Zauberstab aus Versehen gezaubert hat, um die Regal Academy zu verwüsten.

programme.title: Rugrats: Im Spielzeugland, Teil 2
programme.desc: Die Babys besuchen mit ihren Eltern das Feriendorf von Stu. Während sich die Erwachsenen in der Western-Holzhütte einsperren, versucht Angelika Santa Clause seinen Job aufzugeben. Können die Rugrats das angerichtete Chaos wieder in Ordnung bringen?

programme.title: Regal Academy: Weihnachten im Märchenland
programme.desc: Es ist Weihnachten, und Rose freut sich darüber, dass es den Weihnachtsmann wirklich gibt.

programme.title: Max & Ruby: Rubys perfekter Weihnachtsbaum / Die Vogelweihnacht / Max und die Weihnachtsglocke
programme.desc: Ruby möchte den perfekten Weihnachtsbaum finden.//Während Ruby Weihnachtsschmuck bastelt, denkt Max nur an Weihnachtsgeschenke.//Ruby möchte ein Weihnachtslied singen, Max dabei eine ganz große Glocke läuten

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: O Projeto de Natal
programme.desc: Quatro irmãos unem forças para se vingar dos Hagbarts, os valentões mais malvados de sua escola.

programme.title: O Natal Prometido
programme.desc: Quando uma queda de energia causa pânico em uma loja, eles são separados um do outro. Cada um sentiu uma conexão com o outro, mas eles não têm como se reconectar. Com a aproximação do Natal, nem Kim nem Theo podem esquecer o outro.

programme.title: Lucia e o Cristal Mágico
programme.desc: Lucia é a primeira menina da Escola Internacional de Natal. Quando seu melhor amigo, Oscar, é acusado de roubar o cristal mágico do Rei Inverno, que alimenta a máquina atual, Lucia se propõe a provar a inocência dele.

programme.title: Festividades do Chocolate Quente
programme.desc: Colette dirige uma cafetaria conhecida pelo seu chocolate quente secreto e famoso. Marcus, um novo dono de sobremesa, começa a atrair os clientes da Colette, ela está determinada a expô-lo.

programme.title: Bebê a Bordo no Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal”, nem todo mundo parece estar animado para o Natal da Família Chandler.

programme.title: Casamento De Natal
programme.desc: Maggie é uma editora literária cujo hobby é criar oportunidades de relacionamento entre seus amigos. Quando seu ex-namorado aparece como um autor recém-contratado e bem-sucedido, Maggie precisa examinar suas decisões anteriores.

programme.title: O Verdadeiro Sentido do Amor
programme.desc: Na noite de Natal, o xerife Rick parece ter perdido seu espírito natalino. Quando prende um homem acusado de invadir as casas da vizinhança, o xerife não sabe o que fazer quando o invasor declara ser o Papai Noel em pessoa.

programme.title: José e Maria
programme.desc: Em 30a.C., Herodes reinava sob Israel até que o nascimento do Messias ameaçava a sua soberania. Surge então nessa jornada de fé e milagres uma mulher, Maria e um homem, José, escolhidos por de Deus para cuidar daquele que salvaria a humanidade, Jesus.

programme.title: Um Natal em Canaã
programme.desc: Um fazendeiro viúvo do Texas convida seu novo lar para conhecer a família no Natal, apenas para descobrir que as alegrias da temporada mascaram um anseio muito mais profundo.

programme.title: Um Amor Inesperado
programme.desc: É Natal e Sammi está buscando um pouco de sossego. Viciado em trabalho, Seth vem da cidade grande para explorar um terreno que recebeu de herança e que ele pretende vender antes do final do ano. A tranquilidade de Sammi é interrompida pela chegada de Seth

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: A Song for Christmas
programme.desc: Charlotte es nueva en la ciudad y se da la circunstancia de que su madre ha intimado con el padre de la que parece que se va a convertir en su peor enemiga.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: A Vineyard Christmas
programme.desc: Heather, presentadora del popular programa de Tannin TV, está decidida a crear el episodio navideño perfecto presentando una bodega única de su ciudad natal en Vermont, pero choca con el dueño de la bodega.

programme.title: Parejas de navidad
programme.desc: Las mejores amigas Sarah, Cat y Riley se reúnen para disfrutar de la magia navideña con sus familias. Con cada amigo en una encrucijada diferente, todos tendrán que unirse para redescubrir la magia navideña que sucede en la casa de Holly Lane.

programme.title: Homemade Christmas
programme.desc: Cada año, una joven quiere convertirse en la mejor asistente para contratar en Navidad. Pero cuando llega la oportunidad de salvar una fiesta de Navidad y deslumbrar a la persona que le gusta, deberá elegir entre sus aspiraciones y el hombre perfecto.

programme.title: Holiday Joy
programme.desc: Una tímida estudiante de secundaria pide un deseo de Navidad, el tener una familia perfecta, pero cuando su deseo se hace realidad, no es tan perfecto como ella pensó que sería.

programme.title: Christmas Wedding Runaway
programme.desc: Una novia fugitiva hace una búsqueda espiritual cuando es atrapada por la nieve dentro de una cabaña con su abuela y un viejo amor en Navidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.desc: Unendliche Wälder, eine herbe, unversehrte Natur und launisches Wetter prägen den Naturpark Waadtländer Jura. programme.desc: Wasser ist ein Lebenselement, Flüsse sind Lebensadern. Vom Ursprung in den Bergen bis zur Flussmündung lernen wir die Tiere und Landschaften im Herzen Portugals kennen: Hirsche in der Brunft, den seltenen Lynx und den majestätischen Adler.

programme.title: Die Todesküste von Galicien
programme.desc: Die Todesküste von Galicien?Ein Film von Bernd Gerriets und Anuschka SeifertEntenmuscheln sind die begehrtesten Meeresfrüchte Spaniens. Für eine Portion dieser Spezialität zahlen Gourmets in guten Restaurants bis zu 250 Euro. Aber niemand kann die Gefahr bezahlen, der sich die Fischer Galiziens bei der Ernte aussetzen. Ihr Arbeitsrevier ist die Costa da Morte - die Todesküste, an der 2002 der Öltanker Prestige? auseinanderbrach. Hier peitscht der Nordwestwind die Wellen des Atlantiks oft mit Stärke acht gegen die Felsen. Jeder anstürmenden Welle müssen die Männer ausweichen, wenn sie die Entenmuscheln ernten wollen. Für die Fischer sind die Klippen unumgänglich. Denn nur hier können sie dem Meer ihre Beute entreißen. Planet Weltweit begleitet die Entenmuschelfischer bis hinaus zu den lebensgefährlichen Klippen. Aber auch hier werden die Bestände der Entenmuscheln immer kleiner.

programme.title: Freiheit auf Pferderücken
programme.sub-title: Der lange Weg der Nez Perce
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: 1877 weigerten sich rund 750 Angehörige des Stammes der Nez Perce, im Nordwesten der USA, ihre Freiheit aufzugeben und sich in ein Reservat zu begeben. Stattdessen begaben sie sich mit 2.000 Pferden, überwiegend Appaloosas, auf eine abenteuerliche und verlustreiche Flucht über gut 2.000 km quer durch die Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Wasserbüffel gelten in Laos als "Sparbücher für Notzeiten". Muss jemand ins Krankenhaus, geht der Reis aus oder steht eine Hochzeit an, verkauft man einen Büffel. Doch die meisten sind schwach und mangelernährt. Parasiten und Seuchen setzen den Wiederkäuern zu. Innovative Futterblöcke könnten die Situation verbessern.

programme.title: Albanien
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Über viele Jahrhunderte wanderten albanische Hirten mit ihren Tieren über den ganzen Balkan. Diese Tradition fand ein Ende mit der sozialistischen Diktatur. Nach deren Niedergang besannen sich viele der einstigen Schäfer auf ihre alten Bräuche und versuchten auch ihre Kinder für den Hirtenberuf zu begeistern. Haben die Schäfer eine Zukunft?

programme.title: Norwegen, die Rentierprinzessin
programme.desc: Seit Jahrhunderten treten die Sami mit ihren Rentieren in Rennen gegeneinander an: Gezogen von kräftigen Junghirschen rasen die "Rentierprinzessin" Anne Risten Sara und die weiteren Athleten auf Skiern über einen Rundkurs.

programme.title: Die Herren des Lavendels
programme.desc: Frankreichs berühmte Lavendel-Felder. Jahr für Jahr strömen Besucher hierher, angezogen von diesem besonderen Licht, diesem Blau und Lila. Eine Szenerie wie im Traum. Doch hinter der faszinierenden Kulisse ist längst nicht alles perfekt. Wie steht es in Wahrheit um den französischen Lavendel-Anbau? GEO Reportage war vor Ort.

programme.title: Kalmückien
programme.desc: Sanan Matvenov ist erst 26 Jahre alt, doch seit seinem 13. Lebensjahr studiert er die Lehre Buddhas. Mit sieben anderen Mönchen im Alter von 16 bis 26 Jahren lebt er im Goldenen Tempel von Elista, der Hauptstadt Kalmückiens. Im südeuropäischen Teil Russlands, nordwestlich des kaspischen Meeres, lebt das einzige mehrheitlich buddhistische Volk Europas: die Kalmücken. Ihre autonome Republik besteht überwiegend aus Steppe und ist mit knapp vier Bewohnern pro Quadratkilometer extrem dünn besiedelt. Erst seit dem Zusammenbruch der Sowjetunion darf hier der Buddhismus wieder offizieall ausgelebt werden.Planet Weltweit hat den jungen Mönch durch das weitgehend unbekannte Land begleitet.

programme.title: Die scharfen Klingen der Auvergne
programme.desc: Einst gehörte es in die Hosentasche jedes Mannes, in Frankreich wie anderswo, handgefertigt und unverwüstlich, ein markanter und eigenwilliger Alltagsgegenstand: Das Taschenmesser. Das legendäre und unverkennbare Laguiole-Messer hat hier in Zentralfrankreich seine Wurzeln - und seine Meister. Planet Weltweit schaut in die Werkstätten der berühmten Messermeister in einer der atemberaubendsten Regionen Frankreichs.

programme.title: Stilikone Panamahut
programme.desc: Der Panamahut ist der wohl berühmteste Hut der Welt. Dennoch ist über seine wahre Herkunft - er kommt aus Ecuador, nicht aus Panama - und über die aufwendige Kunst des Strohhutflechtens wenig bekannt. Die feinsten Panama Hüte werden auch heute noch von Königshäuptern getragen und Prominente schmücken sich gerne damit. Sie bezahlen Preise von bis zu 10.000 Euro pro Hut, weil sie die Einzigartigkeit und Qualität zu schätzen wissen. Umso erstaunlicher erscheint es da, das die jahrhundertealte Tradition des Strohhutflechtens in Ecuador völlig zu verschwinden droht. Planet Weltweit will das Geheimnis des Panamahutes lüften. programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

programme.title: John Coltrane
programme.sub-title: I want to talk about you
programme.desc: Explore the music of one of the most influential and innovative saxophonists in jazz history: John Coltrane! Immerse yourself in this collection of remarkable performances from the early 1960s that showcase Coltrane's unparalleled artistry and unique sound during a transformative period in the artist's career. Recorded in various European cities, Coltrane is seen playing the songs “Autumn Leaves”, “Hackensack”, “My Favorite Things”, “I Want To Talk About You”, “Vigil”, and “Naima”. Tune in and experience why the music of John Coltrane has touched the lives of so many!

programme.title: Thelonious Monk
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Oscar Peterson Trio, Stuff Smith & Ella Fitzgerald
programme.sub-title: O.P. Trio and E. Fitz. - Jazz At The Philharmonic
programme.desc: The Royal Concertgebouw in Amsterdam is a world-renowned concert hall, known for its first-rate acoustics. It has attracted many famous performers over the years and is one of the Netherlands' most treasured musical institutions. On May 5, 1957, jazz impresario Norman Granz presented his Jazz at the Philharmonic tour at the Concertgebouw in Amsterdam. The Canadian pianist Oscar Peterson and his trio of guitarist Herb Ellis and bassist Ray Brown are later joined by trumpeter Roy Eldridge and drummer Jo Jones. As an added attraction, American violinist Stuff Smith joins the proceedings. American singer Ella Fitzgerald, accompanied by pianist Don Abney, Ellis, Brown and Jones, hits her vocal peak in a stunning set that culminates in a jam session of It Don't Mean A Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing) with the entire ensemble.

programme.title: Charlie Galbraith
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Lenny Kravitz
programme.desc: American singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor and arranger, whose "retro" style incorporates elements of rock, blues, soul, R&B, funk, jazz, reggae, hard rock, psychedelic, pop, folk and ballads. In addition to singing lead and backing vocals, Kravitz often plays all the guitar, bass, drums, keyboards, and percussion himself when recording. He won the Grammy Award for Best Male Rock Vocal Performance four years in a row from 1999 to 2002, breaking the record for most wins in that category as well as setting the record for most consecutive wins in one category by a male.

programme.title: Lynyrd Skynyrd
programme.desc: This film revisits the story of Lynyrd Skynyrd in a manner previously unattempted. Using a mixture of new and archive interviews, contributions from band members and those closest to the group, location shoots, news reports and a fascinating first-hand description of the fateful 1977 plane crash, this program is set to become the standard documentary work on this legendary band.

programme.title: Janis Joplin
programme.desc: Janis Joplin rose to fame in the late 1960s and was known for her powerful, blues-inspired vocals. She died of an accidental drug overdose in 1970. Leading music critics cast fresh light on the career of Janis Joplin.

programme.title: Jefferson Airplane
programme.desc: Jefferson Airplane was a rock band based in San Francisco, California, who pioneered psychedelic rock. Formed in 1965, the group defined the San Francisco Sound and was the first from the Bay Area to achieve international commercial success. They were headliners at the three most famous American rock festivals of the 1960s—Monterey, Woodstock and Altamont—and the first Isle of Wight Festival in England. Their 1967 break-out album Surrealistic Pillow ranks on the short list of most significant recordings of the "Summer of Love". Two songs from that album, "Somebody to Love" and "White Rabbit", are among Rolling Stone's "500 Greatest Songs of All Time." Leading music critics cast fresh light on the career of Jefferson Airplane.

programme.title: Michael Hutchence
programme.desc: Michael Hutchence founding member, lead singer and lyricist of rock band INXS from 1977 until his death on November 22nd 1997. Hutchence was the archetypal rock showman. He exuded an overtly sexual, macho cool with his flowing locks, and lithe and exuberant stage movements. His private life was often reported in the Australian and international press, with a string of love affairs with prominent actresses, models and singers. Hutchence's relationship with UK television presenter Paula Yates began while she was married to musician and Live Aid organiser Bob Geldof. During July of the same year, Hutchence and Yates had a daughter. On the morning of 22 November 1997, Hutchence was found dead in his hotel room in Sydney. His death was reported by the New South Wales Coroner to be the result of suicide.

programme.title: Johnny Cash
programme.desc: Johnny Cash was known by his deep, calm, Bass-baritone voice. His lyrics often contained themes of sorrow, moral tribulation, and redemption. He is one of the best-selling music artists. Known by his signature songs "I Walk the Line", "Folsom Prison Blues", "Ring of Fire", "A Boy Named Sue" along with duet with future wife, June Carter, called "Jackson". Although a Country music icon, his music genre-spanning songs and sound embraced rock and roll, rockabilly, blues, Folk music, and Gospel music. During the last stage of his career, Cash covered songs by several late 20th-century rock artists, notably " Hurt by Nine Inch Nails. Cash died on September 12th, 2003, in Nashville, of complications from diabetes aged 71 just 4 months after the death of his wife. It was suggested that his health worsened due to a broken heart over June's death and was buried next to her in Hendersonville.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer, Budapest Festival Orchestra & Richard Goode
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphonies and Piano Concerto No. 4
programme.desc: Iván Fischer leads his Budapest Festival Orchestra (BFO) in a concert program dedicated to the music of Ludwig van Beethoven. The program opens with the composer's Symphony No. 1 in C major, Op. 21. Afterward, Fischer conducts Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 4 in G major, Op. 58, in which Richard Goode features as the soloist. The acclaimed American pianist (1943) is known for his interpretations of the Beethoven repertoire. Goode recorded all five Beethoven piano concertos with the BFO and Fischer, earning him exceptional critical acclaim and a Grammy Award nomination. As an encore, Goode performs the Sarabande from J. S. Bach's Partita in B-flat major, BWV 825. The program closes with Beethoven's famous Symphony No. 5 in C minor, Op. 67. This performance was recorded at the Béla Bartók National Concert Hall in Budapest, Hungary, on January 29, 2017.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 1 in F major, Op. 18, No. 1 String Quartet No. 10 in E-flat major, Op. 74, "Harp" and String Quartet No. 9 in C major, Op. 59, No. 3, "Razumovsky". This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 13, 2020.

programme.title: Ludwig Wicki, Danish National Symphony Orchestra, DR Junior Choir & Andrea Lykke Oehlenschlæger
programme.desc: Swiss conductor Ludwig Wicki leads the Danish National Symphony Orchestra and the DR Junior Choir in a sparkling concert program of film music. The program features a selection of music from great and Oscar-winning Hollywood films, including Titanic, The Bodyguard, Pirates of the Caribbean, Braveheart, and Moulin Rouge, written by major composers such as John Williams, Hans Zimmer, James Horner, and Klaus Badelt. Highlights include ‘He's a pirate/Davy Jones' from Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest ‘Now We Are Free' from Gladiator ‘My Heart Will Go On' from Titanic and ‘Shallow' from A Star Is Born. Featured soloists in this concert are the young talented singers Andrea Lykke Oehlenschlæger and Diluckshan Jeyaratnam. This performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in May 2022.

programme.title: Pavel Milyukov & Boris Berezovsky
programme.sub-title: Works for violin by Franck, Fauré, Schubert a.o.
programme.desc: Russian violinist Pavel Milyukov and pianist Boris Berezovsky join forces in this concert recorded at Tchaikovsky Concert Hall in Moscow, Russia, on October 15, 2020. Milyukov has won prizes at various international competitions and has appeared at venues throughout Europe. He forms an excellent chamber music duo with acclaimed pianist Boris Berezovsky. On this concert's program are César Franck's Sonata for violin and piano Gabriel Fauré's Après un rêve Alfred Schnittke's Stille Nacht and Franz Schubert's Erlkönig. As an encore, the duo performs ‘Russian Song' from Igor Stravinsky's opera Mavra (arranged by S. Dushkin).

programme.title: Rainbow Reef Relaxation 2
programme.desc: Sit back, relax and enjoy the dazzling world of coral reefs in 4K you embark on a journey through some of the most vibrant underwater reefs on our blue planet - including many scenes which no longer look like this due to coral bleaching. From the cinematographer: "The footage for this film was shot over a period of some years in French Polynesia, Micronesia, Indonesia and East Timor. Unfortunately there are not that vibrant anymore today. Coral reefs have suffered from the rise of water temperature, rise in acidity, destructive fishing methods and severe storms caused by climate change." - Peter Schneider. "Rainbow Reef Relaxation" is a 3-hour long, sweeping yet majestic & vibrant underwater journey to the world's most beautiful lagoons, as captured by Nature Relaxation collaborator Peter Schneider (Underwatercam) paired with ambient underwater sounds and brand new ambient music by the Cynic Project. Filmed in High Definition several years ago, thanks to its age this film offers magical glimpses of an underwater world that is bursting with life, color, and beauty.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler – Wie Tiere schlafen
programme.desc: In der Dokumentation „Wie Tiere schlafen“ geht es um ein noch immer ungelöstes Rätsel der Wissenschaft: Wieso Tiere schlafen müssen, um zu überleben.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler – Wie Tiere durchhalten
programme.desc: Die Dokumentation „Wie Tiere durchhalten“ zeigt in eindrucksvollen Bildern, wie wilde Überlebenskünstler lange Notzeiten überstehen. Hitze, Trockenheit oder strenge Winter machen zahlreichen Arten das Leben schwer.

programme.title: Die Todesküste von Galicien
programme.desc: Die Todesküste von Galicien?Ein Film von Bernd Gerriets und Anuschka SeifertEntenmuscheln sind die begehrtesten Meeresfrüchte Spaniens. Für eine Portion dieser Spezialität zahlen Gourmets in guten Restaurants bis zu 250 Euro. Aber niemand kann die Gefahr bezahlen, der sich die Fischer Galiziens bei der Ernte aussetzen. Ihr Arbeitsrevier ist die Costa da Morte - die Todesküste, an der 2002 der Öltanker Prestige? auseinanderbrach. Hier peitscht der Nordwestwind die Wellen des Atlantiks oft mit Stärke acht gegen die Felsen. Jeder anstürmenden Welle müssen die Männer ausweichen, wenn sie die Entenmuscheln ernten wollen. Für die Fischer sind die Klippen unumgänglich. Denn nur hier können sie dem Meer ihre Beute entreißen. Planet Weltweit begleitet die Entenmuschelfischer bis hinaus zu den lebensgefährlichen Klippen. Aber auch hier werden die Bestände der Entenmuscheln immer kleiner.

programme.title: Freiheit auf Pferderücken
programme.sub-title: Der lange Weg der Nez Perce
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: 1877 weigerten sich rund 750 Angehörige des Stammes der Nez Perce, im Nordwesten der USA, ihre Freiheit aufzugeben und sich in ein Reservat zu begeben. Stattdessen begaben sie sich mit 2.000 Pferden, überwiegend Appaloosas, auf eine abenteuerliche und verlustreiche Flucht über gut 2.000 km quer durch die Rocky Mountains.

programme.title: Laos
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Wasserbüffel gelten in Laos als "Sparbücher für Notzeiten". Muss jemand ins Krankenhaus, geht der Reis aus oder steht eine Hochzeit an, verkauft man einen Büffel. Doch die meisten sind schwach und mangelernährt. Parasiten und Seuchen setzen den Wiederkäuern zu. Innovative Futterblöcke könnten die Situation verbessern.

programme.title: Albanien
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Über viele Jahrhunderte wanderten albanische Hirten mit ihren Tieren über den ganzen Balkan. Diese Tradition fand ein Ende mit der sozialistischen Diktatur. Nach deren Niedergang besannen sich viele der einstigen Schäfer auf ihre alten Bräuche und versuchten auch ihre Kinder für den Hirtenberuf zu begeistern. Haben die Schäfer eine Zukunft?

programme.title: Norwegen, die Rentierprinzessin
programme.desc: Seit Jahrhunderten treten die Sami mit ihren Rentieren in Rennen gegeneinander an: Gezogen von kräftigen Junghirschen rasen die "Rentierprinzessin" Anne Risten Sara und die weiteren Athleten auf Skiern über einen Rundkurs.

programme.title: Die Herren des Lavendels
programme.desc: Frankreichs berühmte Lavendel-Felder. Jahr für Jahr strömen Besucher hierher, angezogen von diesem besonderen Licht, diesem Blau und Lila. Eine Szenerie wie im Traum. Doch hinter der faszinierenden Kulisse ist längst nicht alles perfekt. Wie steht es in Wahrheit um den französischen Lavendel-Anbau? GEO Reportage war vor Ort.

programme.title: Kalmückien
programme.desc: Sanan Matvenov ist erst 26 Jahre alt, doch seit seinem 13. Lebensjahr studiert er die Lehre Buddhas. Mit sieben anderen Mönchen im Alter von 16 bis 26 Jahren lebt er im Goldenen Tempel von Elista, der Hauptstadt Kalmückiens. Im südeuropäischen Teil Russlands, nordwestlich des kaspischen Meeres, lebt das einzige mehrheitlich buddhistische Volk Europas: die Kalmücken. Ihre autonome Republik besteht überwiegend aus Steppe und ist mit knapp vier Bewohnern pro Quadratkilometer extrem dünn besiedelt. Erst seit dem Zusammenbruch der Sowjetunion darf hier der Buddhismus wieder offizieall ausgelebt werden.Planet Weltweit hat den jungen Mönch durch das weitgehend unbekannte Land begleitet.

programme.title: Die scharfen Klingen der Auvergne
programme.desc: Einst gehörte es in die Hosentasche jedes Mannes, in Frankreich wie anderswo, handgefertigt und unverwüstlich, ein markanter und eigenwilliger Alltagsgegenstand: Das Taschenmesser. Das legendäre und unverkennbare Laguiole-Messer hat hier in Zentralfrankreich seine Wurzeln - und seine Meister. Planet Weltweit schaut in die Werkstätten der berühmten Messermeister in einer der atemberaubendsten Regionen Frankreichs.

programme.title: Stilikone Panamahut
programme.desc: Der Panamahut ist der wohl berühmteste Hut der Welt. Dennoch ist über seine wahre Herkunft - er kommt aus Ecuador, nicht aus Panama - und über die aufwendige Kunst des Strohhutflechtens wenig bekannt. Die feinsten Panama Hüte werden auch heute noch von Königshäuptern getragen und Prominente schmücken sich gerne damit. Sie bezahlen Preise von bis zu 10.000 Euro pro Hut, weil sie die Einzigartigkeit und Qualität zu schätzen wissen. Umso erstaunlicher erscheint es da, das die jahrhundertealte Tradition des Strohhutflechtens in Ecuador völlig zu verschwinden droht. Planet Weltweit will das Geheimnis des Panamahutes lüften. Ein Film über die unbekannten Hutflechter von Ecuador.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: El Rey y su hermana, la Princesa Cristina, comparten sus recuerdos de infancia en el palacio. "En realidad no era un entorno agradable para vivir, más bien parecía un hotel", recuerda el Rey al describir las habitaciones donde él y sus hermanas crecieron en el ala sur del palacio. La Princesa Heredera Victoria nos muestra objetos de valor incalculable en sus habitaciones favoritas "Es un patrimonio cultural fantástico y es impresionante que se conserven estos ambientes, teniendo en cuenta lo antiguos que son. Es un tesoro extraordinario y accesible que nos pertenece a todos", afirma. Los espectadores también tienen la oportunidad de adentrarse entre bastidores antes de una visita de Estado, escuchar historias de fantasmas reales, así como a historiadores, expertos y artesanos que nos ofrecen un retrato único de un tesoro nacional: nuestro Palacio Real.

programme.title: Palacio Real de Suecia
programme.desc: Nos subimos a un andamio para averiguar más cosas sobre la renovación de la fachada y llegar al fondo de la cuestión de si el viejo castillo está embrujado. Síganos por los salones dorados y las oscuras bóvedas de los sótanos. El Palacio Real de Estocolmo tiene más de mil habitaciones y cientos de años de historia real. El Rey y su hermana, la princesa Cristina, nos cuentan cómo fue crecer en el palacio. La Princesa Victoria muestra objetos de valor incalculable.

programme.title: Castillo de Windsor: Detrás de los Muros

En 2016, fue nuevamente el epicentro de las celebraciones del 90 cumpleaños de la Reina.

Robusta, cruda e ora anche cotta, questa è l'ultima frontiera culinaria dove uno chef sta ridefinendo il significato di mangiare come un uomo selvaggio. Clienti schizzinosi, cambiamenti climatici bipolari, carenze di cibo e di forniture spesso spingono Bradley all'ultimo grammo della sua sanità mentale, ma questo spirito libero e creativo sembra sempre mantenere la promessa.

programme.title: Desperate Hours
programme.desc: A volte, tutto ciò che serve è uno spostamento sotto i piedi.... Desperate Hours analizza i principali disastri geologici, tra cui le valanghe in Afghanistan, Pakistan, Nepal, Perù e Francia. Vengono inoltre analizzate le frane geologiche nelle Filippine, in India e in Colombia e un'enorme voragine che ha consumato un laghetto in Bosnia. Vengono inoltre analizzate le bufere di neve negli Stati Uniti, in Israele e nel Regno Unito.

programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

programme.title: John Coltrane
programme.sub-title: I want to talk about you
programme.desc: Explore the music of one of the most influential and innovative saxophonists in jazz history: John Coltrane! Immerse yourself in this collection of remarkable performances from the early 1960s that showcase Coltrane's unparalleled artistry and unique sound during a transformative period in the artist's career. Recorded in various European cities, Coltrane is seen playing the songs “Autumn Leaves”, “Hackensack”, “My Favorite Things”, “I Want To Talk About You”, “Vigil”, and “Naima”. Tune in and experience why the music of John Coltrane has touched the lives of so many!

programme.title: Thelonious Monk
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Bootsy Collins
programme.sub-title: Casper the Funky Ghost: Bootsy Collins à Vienne
programme.desc: Bootsy Collins, famed for playing with George Clinton and his very own Rubber Band, is used to playing syncopated, hard and relentlessly rhythmic music. With this unique style Bootsy was a major influence on the development of funk. Now in his 60s, the bassist seems animated by a new energy that reflects his new work on the album ‘Tha Funk Capitol of the World'. With this album, Bootsy Collins pays tribute to the artists with whom he worked during his frantic career: from James Brown and Parliament-Funkadelic to Fatboy Slim. During this concert, recorded at the festival Jazz à Vienne, Bootsy maintains that same energy, giving a spectacular show.

programme.title: Christian Scott
programme.sub-title: Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah, The Walk
programme.desc: In 2019, the vibrant city of Sofia, Bulgaria, hosted the International A to JazZ Festival. Among the featured acts was the trailblazing jazz trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah. This genre-defying artist captivated the audience with his eclectic “stretch music” an approach that incorporates hip-hop and reaches back through the American canon into African percussion and its rich melodic content. Trumpeter Christian Scott aTunde Adjuah's quintet, which includes drummer Corey Fonville, percussionist Weedie Braimah, pianist Lawrence Fields, and bass guitarist Max Mucha, delivered a performance that defied boundaries and expectations.

programme.title: Tony Bennett
programme.desc: Relive the magic of one of the most beloved crooners in music history in his prime: Tony Bennett! Recorded live in London's Royal Albert Hall on March 2, 1974, this enchanting performance showcases Bennett's remarkable vocal prowess and charisma to full effect. Bennett is accompanied by his musical director Torrie Zito and an orchestra of British musicians that includes Kenny Clare (drums), Don Lusher (trombone), and Kenny Baker (trumpet). Tune in for Bennett's captivating take on songs “The Good Things in Life”, “My Favorite Things”, “My Love”, “I've Got Five Dollars”, “It Don't Mean a Thing”, and “Maybe This Time” in this magical concert recording.

programme.title: Oscar Peterson Trio, Stuff Smith & Ella Fitzgerald
programme.sub-title: O.P. Trio and E. Fitz. - Jazz At The Philharmonic
programme.desc: The Royal Concertgebouw in Amsterdam is a world-renowned concert hall, known for its first-rate acoustics. It has attracted many famous performers over the years and is one of the Netherlands' most treasured musical institutions. On May 5, 1957, jazz impresario Norman Granz presented his Jazz at the Philharmonic tour at the Concertgebouw in Amsterdam. The Canadian pianist Oscar Peterson and his trio of guitarist Herb Ellis and bassist Ray Brown are later joined by trumpeter Roy Eldridge and drummer Jo Jones. As an added attraction, American violinist Stuff Smith joins the proceedings. American singer Ella Fitzgerald, accompanied by pianist Don Abney, Ellis, Brown and Jones, hits her vocal peak in a stunning set that culminates in a jam session of It Don't Mean A Thing (If It Ain't Got That Swing) with the entire ensemble.

programme.title: John Coltrane, McCoy Tyner, Elvin Jones & Jimmy Garrison
programme.desc: The mere mention of the name John Coltrane evokes a deeply emotional, often spiritual response from even the most casual jazz fan. Dexter Gordon was a fantastic saxophonist. Miles Davis was a genius. Coltrane stood above - he was a visionary, a saint-like figure. By the standards of most jazz musicians, his life was uneventful. Sure, he had a heroin habit for a while, and Miles Davis punched him, but once he'd experienced the “spiritual awakening” described in the liner notes of his 1965 album A Love Supreme, he dedicated himself to his music with extreme single-mindedness. This broadcast of Coltrane's 1965 performance at the short-lived Belgian jazz festival in Comblain-la-Tour features Trane's classic quartet with Elvin Jones (drums), Jimmy Garrison (bass) and McCoy Tyner (piano).

programme.title: Lenny Kravitz
programme.desc: American singer, songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, record producer, actor and arranger, whose "retro" style incorporates elements of rock, blues, soul, R&B, funk, jazz, reggae, hard rock, psychedelic, pop, folk and ballads. In addition to singing lead and backing vocals, Kravitz often plays all the guitar, bass, drums, keyboards, and percussion himself when recording. He won the Grammy Award for Best Male Rock Vocal Performance four years in a row from 1999 to 2002, breaking the record for most wins in that category as well as setting the record for most consecutive wins in one category by a male.

programme.desc: This film revisits the story of Lynyrd Skynyrd in a manner previously unattempted. Using a mixture of new and archive interviews, contributions from band members and those closest to the group, location shoots, news reports and a fascinating first-hand description of the fateful 1977 plane crash, this program is set to become the standard documentary work on this legendary band.

programme.title: Janis Joplin
programme.desc: Janis Joplin rose to fame in the late 1960s and was known for her powerful, blues-inspired vocals. She died of an accidental drug overdose in 1970. Leading music critics cast fresh light on the career of Janis Joplin.

programme.title: Jefferson Airplane
programme.desc: Jefferson Airplane was a rock band based in San Francisco, California, who pioneered psychedelic rock. Formed in 1965, the group defined the San Francisco Sound and was the first from the Bay Area to achieve international commercial success. They were headliners at the three most famous American rock festivals of the 1960s—Monterey, Woodstock and Altamont—and the first Isle of Wight Festival in England. Their 1967 break-out album Surrealistic Pillow ranks on the short list of most significant recordings of the "Summer of Love". Two songs from that album, "Somebody to Love" and "White Rabbit", are among Rolling Stone's "500 Greatest Songs of All Time." Leading music critics cast fresh light on the career of Jefferson Airplane.

programme.title: Michael Hutchence
programme.desc: Michael Hutchence founding member, lead singer and lyricist of rock band INXS from 1977 until his death on November 22nd 1997. Hutchence was the archetypal rock showman. He exuded an overtly sexual, macho cool with his flowing locks, and lithe and exuberant stage movements. His private life was often reported in the Australian and international press, with a string of love affairs with prominent actresses, models and singers. Hutchence's relationship with UK television presenter Paula Yates began while she was married to musician and Live Aid organiser Bob Geldof. During July of the same year, Hutchence and Yates had a daughter. On the morning of 22 November 1997, Hutchence was found dead in his hotel room in Sydney. His death was reported by the New South Wales Coroner to be the result of suicide.

programme.title: Johnny Cash
programme.desc: Johnny Cash was known by his deep, calm, Bass-baritone voice. His lyrics often contained themes of sorrow, moral tribulation, and redemption. He is one of the best-selling music artists. Known by his signature songs "I Walk the Line", "Folsom Prison Blues", "Ring of Fire", "A Boy Named Sue" along with duet with future wife, June Carter, called "Jackson". Although a Country music icon, his music genre-spanning songs and sound embraced rock and roll, rockabilly, blues, Folk music, and Gospel music. During the last stage of his career, Cash covered songs by several late 20th-century rock artists, notably " Hurt by Nine Inch Nails. Cash died on September 12th, 2003, in Nashville, of complications from diabetes aged 71 just 4 months after the death of his wife. It was suggested that his health worsened due to a broken heart over June's death and was buried next to her in Hendersonville.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer, Budapest Festival Orchestra & Richard Goode
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphonies and Piano Concerto No. 4
programme.desc: Iván Fischer leads his Budapest Festival Orchestra (BFO) in a concert program dedicated to the music of Ludwig van Beethoven. The program opens with the composer's Symphony No. 1 in C major, Op. 21. Afterward, Fischer conducts Beethoven's Piano Concerto No. 4 in G major, Op. 58, in which Richard Goode features as the soloist. The acclaimed American pianist (1943) is known for his interpretations of the Beethoven repertoire. Goode recorded all five Beethoven piano concertos with the BFO and Fischer, earning him exceptional critical acclaim and a Grammy Award nomination. As an encore, Goode performs the Sarabande from J. S. Bach's Partita in B-flat major, BWV 825. The program closes with Beethoven's famous Symphony No. 5 in C minor, Op. 67. This performance was recorded at the Béla Bartók National Concert Hall in Budapest, Hungary, on January 29, 2017.

programme.title: Quatuor Ebène
programme.desc: Renowned French string quartet Quatuor Ébène marked the 250th birth anniversary of Ludwig van Beethoven (1770-1827) with a remarkable project: recording all of the great composer's sixteen string quartets. For five years, violinists Pierre Colombet and Gabriel Le Magadure, violist Marie Chilemme, and cellist Raphaël Merlin immersed themselves in Beethoven's 650 pages of sheet music. Their efforts culminated in the performance of the composer's complete repertoire for string quartet, which covers three decades of Beethoven's musical creativity, during six impressive concerts at Philharmonie de Paris in the autumn of 2020. Quatuor Ébène explored every facet of Beethoven's string quartet repertoire: from the youthful Opus 18 string quartets to the Razumovsky, Harp, and Serioso quartets (Opus 59, 74, and 95) from his middle period, and finally, the depth of his late quartets (Opus 127 to 135). This program features Quatuor Ébène performing Beethoven's String Quartet No. 1 in F major, Op. 18, No. 1 String Quartet No. 10 in E-flat major, Op. 74, "Harp" and String Quartet No. 9 in C major, Op. 59, No. 3, "Razumovsky". This concert performance was recorded at Philharmonie de Paris on October 13, 2020.

programme.title: Ludwig Wicki, Danish National Symphony Orchestra, DR Junior Choir & Andrea Lykke Oehlenschlæger
programme.desc: Swiss conductor Ludwig Wicki leads the Danish National Symphony Orchestra and the DR Junior Choir in a sparkling concert program of film music. The program features a selection of music from great and Oscar-winning Hollywood films, including Titanic, The Bodyguard, Pirates of the Caribbean, Braveheart, and Moulin Rouge, written by major composers such as John Williams, Hans Zimmer, James Horner, and Klaus Badelt. Highlights include ‘He's a pirate/Davy Jones' from Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man's Chest ‘Now We Are Free' from Gladiator ‘My Heart Will Go On' from Titanic and ‘Shallow' from A Star Is Born. Featured soloists in this concert are the young talented singers Andrea Lykke Oehlenschlæger and Diluckshan Jeyaratnam. This performance was recorded at the DR Koncerthuset in Copenhagen, Denmark, in May 2022.

programme.title: Pavel Milyukov & Boris Berezovsky
programme.sub-title: Works for violin by Franck, Fauré, Schubert a.o.
programme.desc: Russian violinist Pavel Milyukov and pianist Boris Berezovsky join forces in this concert recorded at Tchaikovsky Concert Hall in Moscow, Russia, on October 15, 2020. Milyukov has won prizes at various international competitions and has appeared at venues throughout Europe. He forms an excellent chamber music duo with acclaimed pianist Boris Berezovsky. On this concert's program are César Franck's Sonata for violin and piano Gabriel Fauré's Après un rêve Alfred Schnittke's Stille Nacht and Franz Schubert's Erlkönig. As an encore, the duo performs ‘Russian Song' from Igor Stravinsky's opera Mavra (arranged by S. Dushkin).

programme.title: Rainbow Reef Relaxation 2
programme.desc: Sit back, relax and enjoy the dazzling world of coral reefs in 4K you embark on a journey through some of the most vibrant underwater reefs on our blue planet - including many scenes which no longer look like this due to coral bleaching. From the cinematographer: "The footage for this film was shot over a period of some years in French Polynesia, Micronesia, Indonesia and East Timor. Unfortunately there are not that vibrant anymore today. Coral reefs have suffered from the rise of water temperature, rise in acidity, destructive fishing methods and severe storms caused by climate change." - Peter Schneider. "Rainbow Reef Relaxation" is a 3-hour long, sweeping yet majestic & vibrant underwater journey to the world's most beautiful lagoons, as captured by Nature Relaxation collaborator Peter Schneider (Underwatercam) paired with ambient underwater sounds and brand new ambient music by the Cynic Project. Filmed in High Definition several years ago, thanks to its age this film offers magical glimpses of an underwater world that is bursting with life, color, and beauty.
